<TITLE> Ministry allocates Tk 1 crore in youth welfare funds </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 30 (bdnews24.com) - The youth and sports ministry Tuesday allocated Tk 1 crore in youth-orientated welfare funds in a bid to encourage entrepreneurialism and involve the next generation in the development of the country. The decision was taken at a meeting of the Youth Welfare Fund Management Board, chaired by youth and sports adviser Tapan Chowdhury, the government said in a statement. Youth organisations involved in development projects such as fisheries, poultry, sanitation, cottage industries, forestation and anti-drug programmes will be targeted as likely recipients. Organisations registered with the Youth Development Directorate will be given priority. bd
